  "read": "The concrete TileLang dKV branch now has a real speed promotion: widening the route panel to two 512-group panels, increasing token_block to 64, using block_k=64/block_d=64, and launching with 512 threads moves full final-dKV output from 10.956 ms to 8.204 ms at S4096 while preserving S128 final-dKV parity. This is no longer just a memory-contract probe; it reaches the same latency band as the retained Triton sparse-atomic wall while keeping a reduced-row final-output contract. It still depends on diagnostic materialized probs/grad_logits and a PyTorch final fold, so the next integration step is to replace the fold with a small TileLang/rocPRIM reducer or direct compressor-dKV consumer, then fuse LI/probability production for memory/correctness rather than expecting that fusion alone to provide the speedup."
